description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Team Leader within Patient Movement Services on the QMC Campus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Patient Movement Team Leader you will provide effective supervision ensuring a continued professional and responsible service is delivered to meet the needs of the Trust. You will take the lead in the organisation of staff deployment and response to work requests through the allocation of tasks on NerveCentre to ensure consistent provision and effective monitoring of all tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a challenging and demanding post, the successful candidate must be outgoing, enthusiastic and flexible in their approach. They must be able to prioritise conflicting requests and the ability to work under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you have a good standard of English language both written and oral, and have relevant experience of working in a hospital environment. Experience of having worked with NerveCentre is desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours of work will be 37.5 per week between the hours of 6am and midnight, working 5 days a week including Saturdays and Sundays on a rota basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stephen Booth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Asst Facilities Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;stephen.booth3@nuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lauren Moore (lauren.moore@nuh.nhs.uk)&lt;/p&gt;
